{
  "doc_id": "8605",
  "text": "AD patients had significantly higher p-Tau burden compared with controls in ACC and MCC, and compared with DLB in Pr/Cu. While other studies have observed a relationship between lower NFT Braak stage and higher CIS ratios in clinically diagnosed DLB patients (10, 37), we found no such correlation. We also failed to observe a relationship between tau pathological burden in PCC with CIS and perfusion in PCC. The CIS is not specific to DLB and has been shown to be present in posterior cortical atrophy (PCA) [CITATION_1] . A high NFT Braak stage is typically observed in PCA [CITATION_2] , which may reflect differential AD pathology distribution [CITATION_3] and potentially supports our finding of no association between NFT pathology and the CIS.",
